Based on odML terminology http://portal.g-node.org/odml/terminologies/v1.0/experiment/experiment.xml, v.1.0, d. 2012-01-02 http://portal.g-node.org/odml/terminologies/v1.0/dataset/dataset.xml, v.1.0, d. 2015-10-04 http://portal.g-node.org/odml/terminologies/v1.0/protocol/protocol.xml, v.1.0, d. 2014-11-25 http://portal.g-node.org/odml/terminologies/v1.0/event/event.xml, v.1.0, d. 2012-01-02 http://portal.g-node.org/odml/terminologies/v1.0/setup/setup.xml, v.1.0, d. 2012-01-02 http://portal.g-node.org/odml/terminologies/v1.0/recording/recording.xml, v.1.0, d. 2012-01-02 Person state attributes are based on the EEGBase (http://eegdatabase.kiv.zcu.cz/) experiment metadata.

details.purpose: Specification of an experiment. Experiment includes protocol (with dataset, setup and recording parameters), events and person state.

items.items: Specification of an experiment. The Experiment is part of a Project and the recorded data for a specific Experiment are found in Datasets. Possible subsections are, for example, Dataset and Stimulus.
Section for short annotations that are taken during an experiment to describe certain events.
The name of the project this experiment belongs to.
The ID of the project this experiment belongs to.
The person, who created this protocol.
During a recording session in a Setup Datasets are obtained from Cells and/or a Subject by using various stimuli (Stimulus section).
The experimental setup used in the recordings. By using HardwareProperties as a subsection, a very detailed description of the setup can be given.
The location of the setup (e.g. room).
The department where the setup is located.
The person who built the setup.
The person who is responsible for the setup maintanance.
An identifier of the used setup configuration, e.g. if variations of the same setup are used.
The ID of a setup configuration stored e.g. in a database.
The name of the person actually performing the recordings.
If registered in a database the primary key of the person that performed the experiments.
The date and time at which the recording started in (YYYY-MM-DD hh:mm:ss format).
The date and time at which the recording ended in (YYYY-MM-DD hh:mm:ss format).
The date the recording session was conducted (YYYY-MM-DD format).
The date the recording session ended (YYYY-MM-DD format).
The time the recordings began (hh:mm:ss format).
The time the recordings ended (hh:mm:ss format).

Names (URLs) and times of recorded data files. Datasets are obtained during a Recording and may belong to different Experiments. Related sections that can be used as subsections, parent sections, or siblings are Stimulus, HardwareSettings, and Experiment.
A comma separated ascending list of all used values for indicating the overall quality of the dataset. E.g. "poor,fair,good".
A rough indication of the overall quality of the dataset. E.g. poor, fair, or good.
The URL of a data file.

Data of this dataset. Be aware that including the actual content of a data file by this property will blow up the the size of the metadatafile. We rather recommend to simply refer to the URL of a dataset file using the FileURL property.
A comment about the dataset (common to all files belonging to this dataset).
The local time recording was ended.
The local time recording was started.
The date the recording of this dataset was ended.
The date recording of this dataset was started.
The point in time the recording of this dataset was ended.
The point in time the recording of this dataset was started.
